The paper deals with coding schemes for covert communication over channels, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM) categories. The use of non-linearity and multilevel coding also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) and coding theory (cs.CC) categories. Finally, the paper's focus on practical implementation and use of families of codes suggests that it may also be relevant to the signal processing (cs.SI) category.
